column4: <content>Peasant's Dance, Vienna. An echo - rather weak - of it appears in the Peasants at table by R. Savery signed and dated 1608 (during his stay in Prague) (Brussels Museum, Gent. Exh. 1954, N° 11). This agrees with inventory entry ""pauernmusica"" von alten Bruegel."" Similarities: horizontals (hands) across table dancing couple with arm raised in middleground.</content>
